# Design Principles

## Color Palette
Define your primary, secondary, accent colors, and semantic colors (success, error, warning).

Example:
```ts
// In your Tailwind config or CSS variables
primary: hsl(240 65% 60%)
secondary: hsl(220 20% 15%)
accent: hsl(270 70% 65%)
destructive: hsl(0 70% 55%)
```

## Typography
Specify font families, sizes, weights, and line heights for headings and body text.

Example:
- Primary font: Inter (or system font stack)
- Monospace: JetBrains Mono for code/data
- Heading sizes: text-4xl, text-3xl, text-2xl, text-xl
- Body: text-base with line-height 1.5

## Spacing & Layout
Define spacing scale, grid system, and layout patterns.

Example:
- Base unit: 4px (0.25rem)
- Use Tailwind spacing scale: gap-4, p-6, mb-8
- Grid: Use CSS Grid or Flexbox for responsive layouts
- Container: max-w-5xl mx-auto for content width

## Component Patterns
Document common component patterns, glassmorphism effects, animations, etc.

Example:
```tsx
// Card pattern
<div className="p-6 rounded-xl border border-border/30 bg-card">
  {/* Content */}
</div>

// Button with hover
<Button className="hover:bg-primary/90 transition-colors">
  Click me
</Button>
```

## Accessibility
Specify WCAG compliance level, contrast ratios, and keyboard navigation patterns.

- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for text
- Keyboard navigation: All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Focus indicators: Visible focus rings on all interactive elements
- Screen readers: Use semantic HTML and ARIA labels where needed

